dct_title_s: Ægypti recentior descriptio : Ægyptis & Jurcis Elchibith; Arabibus Mesre & Misri, Hebræis Mitsraim
dct_description_sm: Scale 1:2,300,000 ; Relief shown pictorially ; Map oriented with north to the right ; Includes decorative title cartouche with European and Egyptian figures, astronomical instruments, animals and the Pyramids ; Map interior decorated with local fauna, including horses, goats, camels and crocodiles ; Amsterdam : Publisher not identified
dct_rights_sm: The images on this web site, from maps in the collection of the Melville J. Herskovits Library of African Studies and housed in the Government & Geographic Information Collection of Northwestern University Libraries are in the public domain in the United States, and as such, not subject to copyright restriction. The Libraries request users cite both the URL and Northwestern University Libraries if they wish to reproduce images from the repository.
